title: How Much Does a Mobile App Boost Retention Compared to a Website?
text:
I’m curious to hear your experiences in user retention via an app versus a website because we’re considering building one.

Push notifications plus screen real estate and higher barrier to entry naturally make it seem that user retention on apps would be greater than a website. However, hearing anecdotal stories and numbers would be great.

For example, the Whatnot cofounder said one of their major iterations on the way to pmf was a mobile app over a website: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OKD0IAcwMig&t=291s&ab_channel=YCombinator

Thanks!
